The paper deals with cache management in a network, which involves optimizing the placement of content in caches to maximize utility and minimize transmission cost. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), distributed computing (cs.DC), control systems (cs.SY), information theory (cs.IT), and game theory (cs.GT).
